I know this is not a typical post on my feed, but Haiti has a very special place in my heart. I had the opportunity to go with the global orphan project after one of the disastrous hurricanes they had. That trip changed my life. Those kids changed my life. They had such a beautiful outlook on life and desire to be great, despite losing everyone and everything around them. They really taught me so much about resilience, love and life. If you know me, you know I have such a soft spot for kids and they’re the ones that need our help. Haiti is turmoil right now, since the collapse of its government. They’re suffering from cholera outbreaks, gang violence, kidnappings and it’s heartbreaking.  If you’re able to and you find it in your heart to donate, it would mean so much to me. ❤️ Haiti will always have a place in my heart. These are some pictures from my trip. Visit goproject.org  I’ll add a link in my bio. #haiti

This New Year’s Eve I’ll be staying at home with my babies, praying and hoping for the best. My baby girl has a really bad infection and now liver failure. We weren’t ready to let her go, my family (that doesn’t live here in LA) wanted to say goodbye, and I wanted to give her a fighting chance, and I see her fighting. She’s slowly moving around a little bit more. The point is to get rid of this infection so we can target her kidneys next. So I made the choice to take her home administer IV’s daily and give her medicine hoping we can flush it out. I know some people might not understand but this has been a family member to me and by my side through everything in life. I love her so much and nothing else matters to me right now besides her health. So I put it in God’s hands. ❤️
